  <description type="morphology">Plants  terrestrial.  Stems  creeping; tips often somewhat erect.  Leaves  dimorphic; fertile leaves erect, often notably smaller than sterile leaves in length and width.  Blades  1--2-pinnate; pinnae monomorphic to dimorphic, pinnatifid or pinnate.</description>
  <description type="distribution">nearly worldwide, tropical and temperate regions.</description>
  <number>1</number>
  <discussion>Species 10 (3 in the flora):</discussion>
  <key>
    <key_statement>
      <statement_id>1</statement_id>
      <description type="morphology">Fertile leaves with pinnae monomorphic, all spore-bearing; tuft of hairs persistent on abaxial surface of pinnae near base.</description>
      <determination>1 Osmunda cinnamomea</determination>
    </key_statement>
    <key_statement>
      <statement_id>1</statement_id>
      <description type="morphology">Fertile leaves with pinnae dimorphic, some spore-bearing, some not; tuft of hairs absent on abaxial surface of pinnae near base.</description>
      <next_statement_id>2</next_statement_id>
    </key_statement>
    <key_statement>
      <statement_id>2</statement_id>
